le','','matheny.44@osu.edu','6142701825','470',NULL,'matheny.44@osu.edu','97X0EtEwG7Tw6','Ms.','Graduate Fellow','The Ohio State University','Civil, Environmental, and Geodetic Engineering','2070 Neil Avenue','Columbus','43210','','','I will incorporate a plant hydrodynamic subroutine into the CLMED module in effort to improve the simulation of transpiration and the surface energy budget. ',NULL,1,'active',236,36,3,'2015-10-12 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,1,'Ryan Knox, Rosie Fisher, Chonggang Xu, Gil Bohrer',NULL,'2016-10-13 00:00:00','2015-10-12 00:00:00',NULL,NULL),(812,'Lipsa','Dan',NULL,NULL,'dan.lipsa@kitware.com','5188814938',NULL,NULL,'dan.lipsa@kitware.com','68nI/JDRNJZNc','Dr.','R&D Engineer','Kitware',NULL,'28 Corporate Drive','Clifton Park','12065',NULL,NULL,'Software engineering',NULL,1,'active',236,33,1,'2015-10-20 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,1,'Jim Edwards',NULL,'2016-10-21 00:00:00','2015-10-20 00:00:00',NULL,NULL),(813,'Sanderson','Benjamin',NULL,'CCR','bsander@ucar.edu','3034971362','220',NULL,'bsander@ucar.edu','40a68EpRFi0es','Dr','Project Scientist','NCAR','CGD','NCAR Mesa Lab, 1850 Table Mesa Dr','Boulder','80305',NULL,NULL,'Coupled system parameter tuning methodology for CESM2, in particular with relevance to correcting Amazon dry bias in coupled simulations',NULL,1,'active',236,6,8,'2015-11-03 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,1,'David Lawrence',NULL,'2016-11-04 00:00:00','2015-11-03 00:00:00',NULL,NULL),(814,'Qin','Hongchen',NULL,NULL,'hongcheq@uci.edu','949-293-6531',NULL,NULL,'hongcheq@uci.edu','71ryKAhPP09bM',NULL,'Research Assistant','University of California, Irvine','Department of Earth System Science','1101, Croul Hall,\r\nDepartment of Earth System Science,\r\nUniversity of California, Irvine','Irvine','92697',NULL,NULL,'Despite the critical functionalities in energy budget and hydrological balance at the land-atmosphere interface, the accurate understanding and realistic simulations of the coupling between the two are still at rudimentary stage due to the scarcity and quality of observational data, intrinsic limitations of present general circulation models (GCMs) with approximate parameterizations or limited-area models with implicit unidirectionality of feedbacks from large-scale dynamics to local processes. Recent local studies using large eddy simulation-land surface model framework (LES-LSM) manifested that drier soil can produce greater amount of cumulus clouds under relatively weak atmospheric stability mainly because of entrainment processes, illuminating the ability of explicit shallow convections in changing local land-atmospheric feedbacks. The question naturally arises: does explicit shallow convections alter the physics of global land-atmosphere feedbacks? Answering this baffling question requires a GCM with resolved shallow convections, which turns to be a huge challenge due to its demands for gigantic computational power and innovative infrastructure construction.\r\n\r\nWe are able to see the dawn light to address this issue thanks to a technique called superparameterization (SP), namely cloud-resolving models embedded with every grid column of a GCM. SP has been proved to have better performance on convective processes than conventional parameterization methods. Taking the philosophy of SP and targeting boundary-layer turbulent processes, especially marine stratocumulus, ultraparameterization (UP) Community Atmosphere Model (CAM) is developed based on current SPCAM version 5. The objective of the present research is to further develop the UPCAM so that it can successfully simulate continental shallow convections, and to investigate the role of shallow convections in land-atmosphere feedbacks globally.\r\n\r\nThe standard Cloud Resolving Models implemented in SPCAM have 30 levels vertically, 4km in horizontal resolution and 20 seconds in time step. Eventually , We will build the UPCAM with 120 levels, 250m in horizontal resolution and 2 seconds in time step, while make it still computationally affordable with extra strategies. ',NULL,1,'active',236,5,1,'2015-11-04 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,1,'Dr. Mike Pritchard, Dr. Gabe Kooperman, Dr. Hossein Parishani, Dr. Jian Sun ',NULL,'2016-11-20 00:00:00','2017-07-27 00:00:00',NULL,'hongcheq'),(815,'Hendricks','Jonathan','Patrick','DART','hendric@ucar.edu','3034972454','ML 366',NULL,'hendric@ucar.edu','65mOvcTSW1wHY','Mr','Software Engineer','NCAR','IMAGE','1850 Table Mesa Dr','Boulder','80305','1850 Table Mesa Dr',NULL,'I work with the Data Assimilation Research Section and use CESM regularly.  I am interested in access to the CESM repository so I can see the inner workings of the code and understand how the system works as a whole.  HOMME is particularly interesting to me as I have worked Finite Volume Methods for my graduate research and am interested in co-mentoring a PRECIP student next summer with Ram Nair.',NULL,1,'active',236,6,11,'2015-11-09 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,1,'None',NULL,'2016-11-10 00:00:00','2015-11-09 00:00:00',NULL,NULL),(816,'Li','Yinrui',NULL,NULL,'li230@illinois.edu','2176076056',NULL,NULL,'li230@illinois.edu','11smoyKOwll06','Ms','graduate student, research assistant','Department of Atmospheric Sciences, UIUC','Atmospheric Sciences','Atmospheric Sciences Bldg, 103 S Gregory St','urbana','61801',NULL,NULL,'Analyzing the aging process of black carbon based on CAM5 model with MAM3/MAM4 code.',NULL,1,'active',236,14,1,'2015-11-10 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,1,'Under the supervision of Prof. Donald Wuebbles and Prof. Nicole Riemer.',NULL,'2016-11-20 00:00:00','2015-11-10 00:00:00',NULL,NULL),(817,'Xu','Yangyang',NULL,NULL,'yangyang@ucar.edu',' (303) 497-1743',NULL,NULL,'yangyang@ucar.edu','27bomycawaayw',NULL,'postdoc fellow','National Center for Atmospheric Research',NULL,'1850 Table Mesa Driv','Boulder','80305','1850 Table Mesa Driv',NULL,'testing new python-based cesm diagnostic package',NULL,1,'active',236,6,8,'2015-11-12 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,1,'Alice Bertini',NULL,'2016-11-14 00:00:00','2015-11-13 00:00:00',NULL,NULL),(818,