 idealized changes in the land surface (e.g. atmospheric response to a localized change in albedo). Further development of our simplified land model requires access to CAM, so we can get the simple land model working the coupled system. In particular, the TSS software engineers have suggested that I start with CESM_1_5_beta05 or CAM5_4_43. \r\n\r\nUpdate (July 2017): We have built the idealized land model and it runs coupled to CESM. The land model piggy-backs on the infrastructure of CLM5, so as CESM2 evolves we need to update a few files to keep our coupled model working correctly, with the end-goal of coupling it to CAM6 once CESM2 is released. Right now we\'re running coupled to CAM5. ',NULL,1,'active',236,48,3,'2016-03-28 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,1,'NCAR staff member: Gordon Bonan. NSF grant: AGS-1553715',NULL,'2017-03-29 00:00:00','2017-07-27 00:00:00',NULL,'marysalague'),(849,'Schultz','Natalie','Marie','','natalie.schultz@yale.edu','651-210-2468','Room 338',NULL,'natalie.schultz@yale.edu','60mCM7UEfZGiA','Ms.','PhD Student','Yale University','School of Forestry & Environmental Studies','21 Sachem Street','New Haven','06511','','','This work will focus on adding an option for a new soil column configuration for CLM.  Currently, all plant functional types (PFTs) share a single column.  This work will allow the option of separate columns for each PFT.  This new column configuration isolates each PFT from the others, which is useful for both model evaluation/validation and land cover change experiments.      ',NULL,1,'active',236,7,3,'2016-05-20 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,0,'Dave Lawrence, Peter Lawrence',NULL,'2017-05-23 00:00:00','2016-05-22 00:00:00',NULL,NULL),(843,'Chiu','Christine',NULL,NULL,'c.j.chiu@reading.ac.uk','44 0118 378 5574',NULL,NULL,'c.j.chiu@reading.ac.uk','534rgc/gygFXs','Dr','Associate Professor','University of Reading','Meteorology','PO Box 243','Reading','RG6 6BB',NULL,NULL,'We intend to use our synergetic cloud and precipitation retrievals (from rada