e flux and water-use efficiency at US and Europe flux tower sites. ',NULL,1,'active',236,10,6,'2016-08-26 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,1,'Danica Lombardozzi, Bill Sacks',NULL,'2017-09-10 00:00:00','2016-08-26 00:00:00',NULL,NULL),(866,'Grini','Alf','','','alfg@met.no','+4722963340','',NULL,'alfg@met.no','425fpQ7v/.N0E','Dr','researcher','Norwegian Meteorological Institute','','Henrik Mohns plass 1, 0313 Oslo','Oslo','0313','','','I am working as a researcher with NorESM which is quite similar to CESM, but it is a platform for cooperation among Norwegian scientists.\r\n\r\nI am spending a lot of time looking into physics parametrizations developed by Norwegian scientists, and I am incorporating them into NorESM. \r\n\r\nQuite often it is useful for me to look into development versions in order to understand what future versions of CESM will look like.\r\n\r\nMy work has also contributed to finding some bugs in the chemistry parts (reported on email to Francis Vitt). I have done some analysis of the cloud microphysics which led to fruitful discussions with Andrew Gettelman. This work led to a poster presentation in this year\'s Breckenridge meeting. \r\n\r\nMy main contribution in the near future would be to be report possible bugs or inconsistencies in the CAM code, but also possibly to proposed improved physics parametrizations wherever that could be suitable.',NULL,1,'active',165,0,1,'2016-09-02 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,1,'Jean-Francois Lamarque, Andrew Gettelman, Simone Tilmes, Francis Vitt',NULL,'2017-09-10 00:00:00','2016-09-02 00:00:00',NULL,NULL),(867,'Roessler','Thomas','','','roessle9@uwm.edu','1234567890','',NULL,'roessle9@uwm.edu','31Nywgrd63o1o','Mr.','Research Assistant','Univerity of Wisconsin Milwaukee','Mathematical sciences','College of Engineering & Applied Science\r\nEngineering & Mathematical Sciences Building\r\n3200 N. Cramer Street','Milwaukee','53211','','','Test new methods of incorporating subgrid variability into microphysical calculations using SILHS.',